race.comment: Open race to close out the card. PORT RIVER BILLIE (10) was a touch disappointing last time out but the three placings prior were full of merit. Drawn to get a cosy run in transit from gate two and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. SCOUNDREL (4) has a handy record over this distance range with a win and a placing from two attempts. Will be rock-hard fit for this and can play a significant role in the outcome. TRUCK STOP HONEY (13) placed over this track and trip last time out and is usually thereabouts. Top-three contender. Former Waterhouse/Bott galloper SUBDUE (2) shed the maiden tag in the first run for the new stable before being tipped out for time to mature. Keep very safe while fresh.
